# Real-Time Pokédex

A real-time Pokémon classification system that uses a webcam feed to identify 15 different Pokémon and display live Pokédex information including type, abilities, and flavor text.

## How It Works
- Webcam frames are captured and classified every 2 frames using YOLO11s-cls
- A stability buffer of 8 consecutive confident frames prevents flickering
- Once a Pokémon is locked in, metadata is fetched from PokéAPI and displayed in a styled panel
- The web interface is served locally via Flask

## Pokémon Supported
Bulbasaur, Charizard, Squirtle, Pikachu, Eevee, Vaporeon, Snorlax, Gengar, Jigglypuff, Mewtwo, Mew, Dragonite, Arcanine, Lapras, Gyarados

## Model Comparison
| Model | Accuracy | F1 | Size | FPS |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| YOLO11s-cls | 91.5% | 0.92 | 10.5 MB | 126 |
| ResNet50 | 90.9% | 0.91 | 90.1 MB | 172* |
| EfficientNet-B0 | 91.6% | 0.92 | 15.6 MB | 128* |

*GPU tensor throughput only

## How To Run
1. Clone the repo
2. Create and activate a virtual environment
3. Install dependencies: `pip install flask opencv-python ultralytics requests`
4. Run: `python stream.py`
5. Open `http://localhost:5000` in your browser

## Tech Stack
- Python, Flask, OpenCV
- Ultralytics YOLO11s-cls
- PyTorch + torchvision (ResNet50, EfficientNet-B0)
- PokéAPI
- Google Colab (T4 GPU for training)

## Dataset
[1282 Pokemon | 139542 Images | Updated Pokedex Dataset](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/shivanshcoding/1282-pokemon-139542-images-updated-pokedex-dataset) by Shivansh Coding on Kaggle.

## Colab

The colab folder cotaines the notebook that trains the models. The best.pt was derived from there, but it can be rerun to obtain other results that can be compared. All three models were trained in the same notebook on 
the same dataset
